  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ISO / EHS Consultant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\n<p>• Consulting and on Quality, Environmental and Occupational health and safety management systems such as ISO 9001, ISO 14001 and ISO 45001</p>\n<p>• Conducting site visits to identify applicable EHS legal requirements and establishing EHS legal register for companies</p>\n<p>• Conducting internal audits and / or gap studies at relevant sites / organizations.</p>\n<p>• Developing and conducting specialised training courses on environmental, occupational health and safety management and other quality related management systems</p>\n<p>• Ability to develop and build all-rounded business for the company</p>\n<p>• Other ad-hoc duties as assigned by the company Requirements</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<p>• Degree/ Diploma in Engineering or other related disciplines from recognized institutions or equivalent</p>\n<p>• Relevant experience in related consultancy, auditing, training and experienced in implementing management systems and related schemes such as ISO 9001, ISO 14001 and ISO 45001.</p>\n<p>• Trained Internal Auditor on ISO 9001, ISO 14001 and ISO 45001 (preferable).</p>\n<p>• Relevant experience in related consultancy, auditing, training and experienced in implementing other management systems such as ISO 22301, ISO 22000 and ISO 27001 is an added advantage.</p>\n<p>• Proven good procedure writing, reporting writing and presentation skills.</p>\n<p>• Well-rounded team player to build efficiency and foster a strong team environment</p>\n<p>• Excellent communication and interpersonal skills in liaising with other departments and external clients, associates or partners</p>\n<p>• Good time-management skills in meeting project deadlines</p>\n<p>• Possess professional integrity and business ethics</p>\n<p>• Willingness to travel locally to client sites for about 30% of the working duration</p>",
